quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  49,1,"Believers, do not advance before Allah and His Messenger, and fear Allah. Verily Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing.",footnotes:181513:1,footnotes:181514:2
  49,2,"Believers, do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet and when speaking to him do not speak aloud as you speak aloud to one another, lest all your deeds are reduced to nothing without your even realising it.",footnotes:181515:1,footnotes:181516:2
  49,3,"The ones who lower their voices in the presence of the Messenger of Allah are those whose hearts Allah has tested for God-fearing. Theirs shall be forgiveness and a great reward.",footnotes:181517:1
  49,4,"Surely most of those who call out to you, (O Prophet), from behind the apartments, are devoid of understanding."